solution: class Solution {
    public int numSub(String s) {
        final int MOD = 1_000_000_007;
        long res = 0;
        int cur = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '1') {
                cur++;
                res = (res + cur) % MOD;
            } else {
                cur = 0;
            }
        }
        return (int) res;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Traverse the string once, counting consecutive 1s. For each new 1, add the length of the current run (cur) to the result, which counts all new substrings ending at that position. Reset on 0.

